threats.title: Repo permissions
threats.description: Anyone with  access to git repository cna build and deploy any code , as there is no eyes on it.
threats.mitigation: ensure code is reviewed properly by other team members to ensure nothing malicious is merged in

threats.title: Security gate is skipped
threats.description: We have disabled the security gate for now, this will make us not learn about any security defects introduced by new code, when it happens , which coluld lead to problems later on.
threats.mitigation: So, they need to be implemented, atleast fro the new code coming in to ensure new vulnerabilities are not exposed by the developer

threats.title: JWT token not verified
threats.description: Since we are not checking if the jwt token is verified when updating information in the db, anyone can pretend to be like us and do malicious activity

threats.title: User/vi api exposes applciation to SQL injection
threats.description: since the api doesn't use prepared statements, anyone can exploit it perform sql injection attacks.
threats.mitigation: use prpeared statements so a hacker can't get into our system and updated or get access to priavte data
